Privacy Policy

LumiKidz
Effective Date: 17 October 2024

At LumiKidz, we are committed to protecting the privacy and security of our users, especially children. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share personal information when you use our mobile app, LumiKidz. By using the app, you agree to the practices described in this policy.

1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information:

Personal Information: We do not require users to provide personal data such as names, addresses, or contact details. However, parents or guardians may provide certain information, like an email address, for account creation or app management.
Automatically Collected Information: We may collect non-personal information about how the app is used, including app settings, device type, operating system, and crash reports. This helps us improve our services.
Content You Upload: The app allows users to upload images, sounds, and text to enhance the learning experience. This content is stored locally on your device and not shared with any third-party services unless explicitly stated.
2. How We Use Information
The information collected is used for the following purposes:

To provide and improve the functionality of the app.
To enhance the user experience and customize features.
To diagnose technical issues and improve performance.
3. Sharing of Information
We do not share personal data with third parties, except in the following cases:

Legal Requirements: We may disclose information if required by law or to protect our legal rights.
Service Providers: We may share anonymized data with trusted third-party service providers for analytics and app performance monitoring.
4. Children's Privacy
LumiKidz is designed for children with the guidance and supervision of parents or guardians. We comply with the Childrenâ€™s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and do not knowingly collect personal data from children under the age of 13 without parental consent. Parents can contact us at [insert contact email] to review or delete any personal information we may have collected from their child.

5. Data Security
We take reasonable measures to protect the information collected through the app. However, no method of electronic storage or transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted within the app, and the effective date will be updated. We encourage you to review the policy periodically.

